author: Michael Thein
text:
I‚Äôve had an amazing experience at Anytime Fitness Geylang Central! üí™

Special thanks to Brandon, who has been extremely professional, friendly, and motivating. He always takes the time to guide me with proper techniques and provides great advice on training and lifestyle improvements. His positive energy makes every workout enjoyable and productive.

The gym itself is well-maintained, clean, and equipped with everything you need for a great workout‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs cardio, strength, or functional training. The staff are approachable, and the community here is welcoming and supportive.

Highly recommend this branch and especially Brandon if you‚Äôre looking for someone who genuinely cares about your progress and fitness journey. üëè

author: John Carlo De Jesus
text: A big thanks to Brandon for generously giving his time to guide me toward my goal. i never felt rushed during our session, and i learned so much from him - he is also very friendly. Plus, the place is spacious and the equipment is complete. Excited to try out everything i learned from him!!

author: Kim Ricafort
text: great gym, super spacious and equipment is well maintained. it looks relatively new so i really enjoy frequenting this gym. no toilets within the gym itself but there‚Äôs one right outside on the same level. great variety of equipment and staff was really friendly when i was there the first time. highly recommended.

author: Jeremiah Su
text:
Good amenities, good people, good equipment, clean, spacious, no weirdo gymbros (not at the timings that I go anyway), and staff are really easy to talk to.

Recently they amped up their security so it‚Äôs more secure to come anytime, not too sure about late hours of the night though but will wait and see.

Highly recommended!

author: Nineesha Somaja
text: Best gym to go in Singapore. Friendly staff and good service. Easy to access. Having a great experience. And a good street view from up here.

author: Alexander Aaltonen
text: Recently opened AF outlet, must say one of the best ones around! Good variety of equipment and machines. The only minor bad thing is that there's no restroom, there's a common one but need to leave the gym to access. Still an awesome gym!!

author: Lucien Lim
text:
Spacious, new (as of April 2023) branch of AF that is well equipped and maintained. It has 3 racks (cages) and a smith machine allowing for ample usage opportunities.

It‚Äôs located on the fourth floor, with elevators accessible at the back (right hand side) of the supermarket. The toilet is not attached, so gym goers would have to leave the gym to use the loo (on the same floor).

author: Jeremy Chan
text:
I‚Äôve taken it upon myself to check out the Anytime Fitness gyms around my residence(Tanjong Rhu) @ I‚Äôm glad to say this gym definitely deserves 5 stars. Apart from the entire gym having full windows on all the walls so you have a panoramic view whilst working out, it also has sufficient equipment for an amazing workout.

AF @ Chai Chee still has the most amount of equipment I would say, but this gym, like I said, is more than adequate to enjoy a thorough workout. Closer to me too! :)

Equipments are all new & in pristine condition, gym is clean & pretty large for AF standards(slightly smaller than AF Chai Chee. Check this gym out guys. 5 stars for sure.

author: Boris Tan
text: Gym is well maintained and the staff are super friendly. The machines are widely spaced and it never feels too cramped. 10/10 would recommend!

author: Bobby Chin
text: I have been a member of this gym for six months, and I couldn‚Äôt be happier with my experience. The facility is always clean, well-maintained, and equipped with top-of-the-line equipment. Highly recommend this gym to anyone looking for a supportive and professional environment to work out

Overall, this gym offers a fantastic environment for anyone looking to improve their fitness. I highly recommend giving it a try!

author: Grey Blanket
text: This gym impresses with its clean facilities and well-equipped workout areas. The cardio section features treadmills for those looking to get their heart rate up. Strength training enthusiasts will appreciate the three squat racks available. The friendly staff adds to the positive atmosphere, making it a welcoming environment for both newcomers and seasoned gym-goers alike. Overall, this gym offers a solid experience for those seeking a quality workout space.

author: Stefan N
text: One of my favourite anytime fitness in Singapore. Good selection of machines and free weights. The gym is also not too crowded compared to other af gyms. Toilet is outside the gym but that's only a minor inconvenience. Overall the only thing I would love to see is a chest supported t-bar row.

text: This gym is the cleanest I‚Äôve ever been to! It‚Äôs one of the tidiest clubs around. Members are required to use towels for personal hygiene, so you won‚Äôt see people dripping sweat all over the floor. The staff and members are quite friendly, without the arrogance you sometimes find at other gyms. No muscle men hogging multiple machines here. Highly recommend!

text:

Only issue I had was one of this member in this photo. For regular AF Geylang Central members, you will recognise this person. Narcissistic rude member who ask for dumbells and machines when i was halfway through my workout.

When he comes with his wife, you will see their motorbike gears hogging the shelves. And they‚Äôre never seem to wear pants their age.

Now they have moved to AF Guillemard, I might be back more often at AFGC ‚ò∫Ô∏è

10/10 for both staffs!

author: Quan
text: Excellent gym with everything you need. Staff ensures gym equipments are cleaned daily and are consistently asking for feedback on how to improve. I signed up as a member since the day it opened and recommend this gym to everyone.

author: tarlo gill
text: I chanced upon this gym while on my way back home from office. The space and equipment here are larger than the other AF gyms I visited, so that's definitely something worth noting. Shout out to the team, especially Cory, for providing a free trial and walking through the space in detail. One advantage of this gym is its well-maintained equipment, with plenty of racks and deadlift spots for compound movement. This reduces the waiting time significantly. While you run, the threadmill offers a view of the busy street life outside, so you're sure not to be bored. The shower facilities and bag storage are conveniently located in the middle of the gym, ensuring a hassle-free showering experience. All in all, it's worth checking this place out!

author: daniel
text: The gym is generally well-equipped. To cater to powerlifters, considering adding powerlifting bars alongside the existing deadlift platforms would be beneficial. The functional area impresses with its assortment of bands and rollers for warm-ups. Enhancements could include introducing a wider range of 5-25kg plates for members. Improving the restroom experience by ensuring better air freshening could be appreciated. Lastly, increasing the availability of sanitizers and encouraging the use of towels for equipment cleaning instead of tissues would enhance convenience.
